ef=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">s</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Finset/Card.html#Finset.card\">card</a></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/KrullsHeightTheorem.html#Ideal.height_le_card_of_mem_minimalPrimes_span_finset","kind":"theorem","line":222,"name":"Ideal.height_le_card_of_mem_minimalPrimes_span_finset","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/KrullsHeightTheorem.lean#L222-L227"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/KrullsHeightTheorem.html#Ideal.height_le_spanRank_toENat_of_mem_minimal_primes\"><span class=\"name\">Ideal</span>.<span class=\"name\">height_le_spanRank_toENat_of_mem_minimal_primes</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">R</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Ring/Defs.html#CommRing\">CommRing</a> <span class=\"fn\">R</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Noetherian/Defs.html#IsNoetherianRing\">IsNoetherianRing</a> <span class=\"fn\">R</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">I </span><span class=\"fn\">p</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/Defs.html#Ideal\">Ideal</a> <span class=\"fn\">R</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hp</span> : <span class=\"fn\">p</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Membership.mem\">∈</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">I</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/MinimalPrime/Basic.html#Ideal.minimalPrimes\">minimalPrimes</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">p</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/Height.html#Ideal.height\">height</a></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/SetTheory/Cardinal/ENat.html#Cardinal.toENat\">Cardinal.toENat</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Module/SpanRank.html#Submodule.spanRank\">Submodule.spanRank</a> <span class=\"fn\">I</span>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"**Krull's height theorem** (also known as **Krullscher Höhensatz**) :\nIn a commutative Noetherian ring `R`, any prime ideal that is minimal over an ideal generated\nby `n` elements has height at most `n`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/KrullsHeightTheorem.html#Ideal.height_le_spanRank_toENat_of_mem_minimal_primes","kind":"theorem","line":167,"name":"Ideal.height_le_spanRank_toENat_of_mem_minimal_primes","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/KrullsHeightTheorem.lean#L167-L220"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/KrullsHeightTheorem.html#Ideal.mem_minimalPrimes_span_of_mem_minimalPrimes_span_insert\"><span class=\"name\">Ideal</span>.<span class=\"name\">mem_minimalPrimes_span_of_mem_minimalPrimes_span_insert</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">R</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Ring/Defs.html#CommRing\">CommRing</a> <span class=\"fn\">R</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Noetherian/Defs.html#IsNoetherianRing\">IsNoetherianRing</a> <span class=\"fn\">R</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">q </span><span class=\"fn\">p</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/Defs.html#Ideal\">Ideal</a> <span class=\"fn\">R</span></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">q</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/Prime.html#Ideal.IsPrime\">IsPrime</a></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hqp</span> : <span class=\"fn\">q</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LT.lt\">&lt;</a> <span class=\"fn\">p</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">x</span> : <span class=\"fn\">R</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">s</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Set/Defs.html#Set\">Set</a> <span class=\"fn\">R</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hp</span> : <span class=\"fn\">p</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Membership.mem\">∈</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/Span.html#Ideal.span\">span</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Insert.insert\">insert</a> <span class=\"fn\">x</span> <span class=\"fn\">s</span>)</span>)</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/MinimalPrime/Basic.html#Ideal.minimalPrimes\">minimalPrimes</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">t</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Set/Defs.html#Set\">Set</a> <span class=\"fn\">R</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">htq</span> : <span class=\"fn\">t</span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#HasSubset.Subset\">⊆</a> <span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">q</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hsp</span> : <span class=\"fn\">s</span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#HasSubset.Subset\">⊆</a> <span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/Span.html#Ideal.span\">span</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Insert.insert\">insert</a> <span class=\"fn\">x</span> <span class=\"fn\">t</span>)</span>)</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/Operations.html#Ideal.radical\">radical</a></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">q</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Membership.mem\">∈</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/Span.html#Ideal.span\">span</a> <span class=\"fn\">t</span>)</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/MinimalPrime/Basic.html#Ideal.minimalPrimes\">minimalPrimes</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If `q < p` are prime ideals such that `p` is minimal over `span (s ∪ {x})` and\n`t` is a set contained in `q` such that `s ⊆ √span (t ∪ {x})`, then `q` is minimal over `span t`.\nThis is used in the induction step for the proof of Krull's height theorem. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/KrullsHeightTheorem.html#Ideal.mem_minimalPrimes_span_of_mem_minimalPrimes_span_insert","kind":"theorem","line":129,"name":"Ideal.mem_minimalPrimes_span_of_mem_minimalPrimes_span_insert","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/KrullsHeightTheorem.lean#L129-L164"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span c